  <summary date="2020-01-25T18:22:25Z" status="Introduced in House">Vaccination Information and Promotion Act of 2019 or the VIP Act of 2019

This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services to develop a program to improve the national rate of childhood vaccinations, including a public-awareness campaign and a grant program that supports vaccine education.

Additionally, the Government Accountability Office must study and report on changes in public attitudes toward childhood vaccinations.</summary>
